<title>JAPAN: Nojima says to buy back shares up to 100 mln yen.</title>
<headline>Nojima says to buy back shares up to 100 mln yen.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's Nojima Co Ltd said on Monday it plans to spend up to 100 million yen to buy back up to 70,000 of its own shares.</p>
<p>The aim is to introduce a stock option system, the company said in a statement. Options give holders the right to buy shares at a set price within a certain period.</p>
<p>Nojima operates large-scale retail stores selling electronic appliances for the home.</p>
